<ref name="ml1975-chs25">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|loc={{nobr|chs. "25. The}} Self Appointed Apostles"{{en dash}}{{nobr|"26. The}} First Manifestation" {{pp.|210|226}} {{interp|cumulative}}}}.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p74a">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=74}}. "Not all of them {{interp|i.e. OSE members}} Theosophists".</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p74b">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=74}}. "Neither the Theosophical Society nor the Order of the Star ever seemed to be prevented from carrying out any of their projects through lack of funds".</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p84">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=84}}.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p125">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=125}}. Nitya was appointed following the resignation of Wodehouse.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p129">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=129}}. Many of those present attended at great financial cost, according to Krishnamurti biographer [[Mary Lutyens]].</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p223">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=223}}. The 1925 Theosophical Convention took place on the 50th{{nbsp}}anniversary of the founding of the Theosophical Society. There were high expectations among Theosophists and Star members, mainly due to rumors of significant imminent manifestations related to the World Teacher. The Convention attracted large crowds and wide representation by the international media.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p241">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=241}}. Statement by Besant to the [[Associated Press]].</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p257">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=257}}. A Krishnamurti speaking appearance at the [[Hollywood Bowl]] (Los Angeles) on {{nobr|15 May 1928}} was attended by 16,000 people. His subject was "Happiness through Liberation".</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-p272">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|p=272}}.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp1">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|pp=1, 20{{en dash}}21}}.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp11">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|pp=11{{en dash}}12, 46}}.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp23">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|pp=23{{en dash}}24}}. Leadbeater proclaimed his [[clairvoyance]] as a matter of fact; this was accepted by many Theosophists. [[Reincarnation]] is considered a fundamental doctrine in [[Theosophy (Blavatskian)|Theosophy]]. Besides Krishnamurti, Leadbeater assigned names with Esoteric Theosophical significance to several other actors in the "lives of Alcyone".</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp42">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|pp=42{{en dash}}46}}. "George Arundale {{interp|appeared as}} Fides in ''The Lives of Alcyone''". The CHC had been co-founded by Annie Besant and counted several prominent Theosophists among its faculty and staff.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp46">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|pp=46, 125, 227}}. Ernest Armine Wodehouse, an educator and brother of the poet and writer [[P.G. Wodehouse]], was another prominent Theosophist.</ref>

<ref name="ml1975-pp62">{{harvnb|Lutyens|1975|loc=pp.{{nbsp}}62, {{nobr|ch. "8. The}} Lawsuit" 64{{en dash}}71, 82, 84}}.</ref>

